I’ve ruled out a benchmark leak and I’m keeping this iteration narrow. The fix I’m applying is a small contrastive seed set: paired `CLARIFICATION` and `DIRECT_ANSWER` examples using overlapping verbs like “explain,” “break down,” “compare,” and “help me choose,” so the next run learns the vague-vs-specific boundary instead of just memorizing more vague prompts.
